-- Turkey's Vakifbank obtains one-year syndicated loan worth $850 mln 
-- 
-- Tue Sep 23, 2014 07:13AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 23 (Reuters) - Turkey's state-run lender Vakifbank obtained a 1-year syndicated loan of 528.8 million euro ($681.4 million) and $168.5 million, it said on Tuesday.

The bank said to the Istanbul stock exchange that the loan would be used to finance foreign trade and cost Libor, Euribor + 0.9 percent.